This is an optional input file. 
It provides information of the intraday variability of ground pressure and
temperature for the invers-code for different times of the day.
The differnt values are given in three columns:

time:
The specified time needs to refer to the same time zone as used in the OPUS file.

pressure:
The pressure as measured at the observer needs to be inserted at hPa. The daily
average of the tabellated p should closely match with the ground pressure used
in the pcxs calculation (witin a few hPa).
 
T_PBL: 
For the Temperature T, a change with respect to the reference Temperature
specified in the pcxs input needs to be specified in the third column.
Note that this dT is intended to describe the change of the
Planetary Boudary Level (PBL) Temperature T.
This variation is significantly less than the T rise measured at ground level
during the day. If no information is available, use 0.0.

time pressure T_PBL
$
%p_lines%
***
